"```json\n{\n  \"Coding Problem\": \"Subodhians are taught to add multi-digit numbers from right-to-left one digit at a time.\\nMany find the \\\"carry\\\" operation - in which 1 is carried from one digit position\\nto be added to the next - to be a significant challenge.  Your job is to\\ncount the number of carry operations for each of addition problem so that educators may assess their difficulty.\\n\\nFor the input first line contains n number of records which is less then 1000. And then each line contains two numbers with spacing between them as shown in sample. \\n\\nSAMPLE INPUT\\n3\\n123 456\\n555 555\\n123 594\\n\\nSAMPLE OUTPUT\\nNo carry operation\\n3 carry operations\\n1 carry operation\\n\\nExplanation\\n\\nEXAMPLE 1:-\\n\\nwhen the digits are added then there is no carry found as 3+6=9,2+5=7 and 1+4=5.\\n\\nEXAMPLE 2:-\\n\\nwhen the digits are added then carry is generated as 5+5 =10 so carry is found 3 times.\\n\\nEXAMPLE 3:-\\n\\nwhen the digits 9 and 2 are added only then carry is found so 1 time only.\",\n  \"Ground Truth Solution\": \"for _ in range(int(input())):\\n\\tH,M=input().split()\\n\\tx=list(map(int,H))[::-1]\\n\\ty=list(map(int,M))[::-1]\\n\\tcarry=0\\n\\tans=0\\n\\tfor i in range(len(x)):\\n\\t\\tif x[i]+y[i] + carry>9:\\n\\t\\t\\tcarry+=1\\n\\t\\t\\tans+=1\\n\\n\\t\\telse:\\n\\t\\t\\tcarry=0\\n\\n\\tif ans==0:\\n\\t\\tprint(\\\"No carry operation\\\")\\n\\n\\telif ans==1:\\n\\t\\tprint(\\\"1 carry operation\\\")\\n\\n\\telse:\\n\\t\\tprint(ans,\\\"carry operations\\\")\",\n  \"LLM CoT Steps Breakdown\": \"- Reading Input: Read the number of test cases n and then read each pair of numbers as strings.\\n- Preprocessing: Convert the numbers to lists of digits and reverse them so that the least significant digits are first.\\n- Addition and Carry Tracking: Add the digits from right to left, keeping track of the carry.\\n- Output: Print the number of carry operations in the specified format.\",\n  \"LLM Questions\": [\n    \"How should I handle the input of multiple test cases?\",\n    \"How do I convert the input strings into usable numerical data?\",\n    \"How can I efficiently track and count carry operations during addition?\",\n    \"What is the best way to format the output based on the number of carry operations?\"\n  ],\n  \"Expected Answers to LLM Questions\": [\n    \"Use a loop that iterates n times, where n is the number of test cases provided in the first line of input.\",\n    \"Split the input string into two numbers, then convert each number into a list of integers representing its digits. Reverse each list to process from right to left.\",\n    \"Initialize a carry variable to 0 and an answer variable to 0. During addition, if the sum of the digits plus the carry is greater than 9, increment the answer and set carry to 1. Otherwise, set carry to 0.\",\n    \"If the answer is 0, print \\\"No carry operation\\\". If the answer is 1, print \\\"1 carry operation\\\". If the answer is greater than 1, print the answer followed by \\\"carry operations\\\".\"\n  ]\n}\n```"